# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# DN Notification — environment variables
# Copy to .env and fill in real values. The .env file is loaded
# by docker compose (env_file: .env) and by the app via pydantic.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Telegram API credentials (https://my.telegram.org/apps) ──
TG_API_ID=123456
TG_API_HASH=your_api_hash_here
TG_PHONE=+1234567890
TG_SESSION_NAME=telegram_session

# ── Server ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
HOST=0.0.0.0
PORT=8000
HOST_PORT=8000
LOG_LEVEL=INFO

# ── Security ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Random string. The API rejects requests without a matching
# X-API-KEY header. Rotate periodically.
API_KEY=your_secret_api_key_here

# ── Search ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SEARCH_LIMIT_PER_CHAT=200
SEARCH_TOP_MATCHES=3
SEARCH_CACHE_TTL=300

# ── Persistent storage (in-container) ────────────────────────
# All persistent data lives under this single directory inside
# the container. The host bind-mount in docker-compose.yaml maps
# /var/lib/dn-notification on the host onto the same path inside
# the container. Voices, session, and logs are derived from
# DATA_DIR automatically by the app (no need to set them here).
DATA_DIR=/var/lib/dn-notification

# ── Release / CI (CI-only — NOT read by the running app) ─────
# These variables exist here so a developer running semantic-release
# locally knows the names. In CI the real values come from GitHub
# Actions secrets, never from this file. The production install
# (dnnotification.sh install) does not need them and they are
# ignored at runtime.
#
# GH_TOKEN:           GitHub PAT or fine-grained token with
#                     `contents: write` for the target repo. Used
#                     by semantic-release to push the release
#                     commit, tag, and GitHub Release.
# DOCKERHUB_USERNAME: Docker Hub account that owns
#                     `digitalneetwork/dn-notification`.
# DOCKERHUB_TOKEN:    Docker Hub access token (not the account
#                     password) with `Read, Write, Delete` scope
#                     on the dn-notification repo.
#
# The dnnotification.sh `update` command also reads GITHUB_TOKEN
# (optional) to authenticate GitHub Releases API requests when
# unauthenticated rate limits are exhausted. Leave unset otherwise.
#
# GH_TOKEN=
# DOCKERHUB_USERNAME=
# DOCKERHUB_TOKEN=
# GITHUB_TOKEN=

